To further confirm the surface state and elemental composition of the CQDs, XPS analysis was conducted. As shown in Fig. 4
                           (a), three sharp peaks are observed at 287, 402, and 531 eV, corresponding to the 1s electron binding energies of C, N, and O atoms, respectively, and indicating that the CQDs contain each of these elements. Peak-splitting analysis was conducted on the C 1s peak (Fig. 4(b)); the peaks at 284.60, 285.85, and 287.80 eV suggest that the CQDs contain three different types of carbon atoms, corresponding to those in CC/CC/CH, CO, and CN chemical bonds (the relative contents are shown in Table 1
                           ). The XPS analysis results are consistent with the FT-IR characterization results.
